The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Kirilenko to play in Bangalore 
                                                   Kirilenko to play in Bangalore 
                      
	Bangalore: Maria Kirilenko is all set to be a major attraction at the Bangalore Open tier-II event to be held from March 3-9.         
	Maria will be vying for honours with Williams sisters  Venus and Serena. The other major contenders in the field are Patty Schnyder, Agnes Szavay and Sybille Bammer.         
	I have been to India before for some WTA Tours. I have played some exciting tennis in India. My experience there should give me a little edge over my opponents. I am keenly looking forward to an exciting tournament, she said in a statement here.         
	The Bangalore Open has total prize money of $600,000 and the champion will take home $95,500 and 300 WTA points.         
	Kirilenko had played in the Calcutta Open last year.           (PTI)                                                                                                                   
